Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.41,0:00:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We discovered that all of the great minds that have ever lived calibrate in the mid-400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual reality starts 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.99,0:00:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we asked, well, we can see that man has spent thousands of years trying to define truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.56,0:00:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and so far has not succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.75,0:00:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite all the erudition throughout all the centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no conclusive definition of what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.99,0:00:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.73,0:00:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because without understanding consciousness itself, no definition of truth is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.64,0:00:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, truth, as we commonly think of it, is form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:00:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All duality is form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.68,0:01:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, this is what we think is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.56,0:01:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.60,0:01:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.62,0:01:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a this causing a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.84,0:01:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We arbitrarily call this an event.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.44,0:01:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no events.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.12,0:01:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.30,0:01:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When would an event start?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.96,0:01:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it starts when you decide it will start.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.84,0:01:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When does it end?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.66,0:01:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It decides when you decide it will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.00,0:01:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So there isn't such a thing out there as event.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.36,0:01:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's, again, a mental phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.69,0:01:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is content.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.37,0:01:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the content, which is the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.22,0:01:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's linear and it's form.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.70,0:01:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Linear form is content.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.14,0:01:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Definable, statable, arguable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.34,0:01:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you cannot understand truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.15,0:01:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you talk about the physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.03,0:01:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't understand truth unless you talk about the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.75,0:01:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because truth is only true under certain circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.75,0:01:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances, then, are the proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:02:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where philosophic and political fallacy abounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.23,0:02:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The failure to state under what conditions such and such a thing is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's bad if this was a time of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not bad if it's a time of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.81,0:02:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So failure to state whether you're at war or at peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.01,0:02:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, is the basis of the whole argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.20,0:02:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A thing is true, then, defined as its linear content
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and its proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's true in one circumstance is false in another.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.48,0:02:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And much political polemics is based on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.52,0:02:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,purposely misstating proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.26,0:02:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The proximate field is such and such a law.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.85,0:02:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it just or unjust?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.34,0:02:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it infringing our rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.48,0:02:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it infringing our rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.50,0:02:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on whether you're at war or not, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.50,0:02:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on whether you're in the army or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.57,0:03:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of circumstances change what seems good, the bad, and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the obligation of the government?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.02,0:03:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it just to attack attackers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it obligated to defend the innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is its prime obligation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.50,0:03:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's morally deficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.30,0:03:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The failure to protect the innocent is equally morally deficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.48,0:03:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.48,0:03:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how the proximate field makes what seems moral or immoral
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.54,0:03:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.54,0:03:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Under what circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.54,0:03:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we call that, generally, situational ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.54,0:03:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A thing is true or not true, moral or not moral,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.83,0:03:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We still don't have the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.06,0:03:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the likelihood of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the content under certain circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.09,0:03:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we still need the infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.09,0:03:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so beyond the linearity of a statement
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.60,0:04:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the situation, the time, the era,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.60,0:04:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what century you're talking about, what's culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.60,0:04:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then beyond that is the infinite field,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the nonlinear infinite field of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.86,0:04:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all things are only true to a relative degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.86,0:04:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on circumstances and as compared to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissistic ego hates the thought of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissistic ego rebels against the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.71,0:04:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is anything greater than itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.96,0:04:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it hates whoever's in charge of whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.63,0:04:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it hates God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.37,0:04:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the narcissistic ego is secular, atheistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.37,0:04:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it hates all authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.37,0:05:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it vilifies whatever authority
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.37,0:05:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,happens to be present at the present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.66,0:05:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's done vilifying the present authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it will move on to the next authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.78,0:05:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Substituting people at the top of the heap doesn't help any.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when this one gets fired,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.45,0:05:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll hate the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.45,0:05:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called vilifying the leader, whoever the leader is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.45,0:05:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any difference who the leader is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.67,0:05:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain contingent of society will inevitably hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.67,0:05:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.93,0:05:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.93,0:05:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.93,0:05:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you hate somebody who's on top,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.93,0:05:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find a thousand reasons to hate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.93,0:05:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to rationalize them and justify them,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.93,0:05:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're unfair, unjust, etc., etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how then,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.31,0:05:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is only true within a certain context,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.31,0:05:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,time, place, conditions, certain weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.89,0:05:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,certain cultural setting, certain generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:05:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's true to the generation I grew up in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.89,0:06:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is not true to this generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.89,0:06:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not true to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.37,0:06:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What we all lived by, died for, is not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.72,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.72,0:06:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We consider what they believe in not worth dying for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't die for child pornography,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.03,0:06:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,do a parade about the rights of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to watch child pornography
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,while the taxpayer pays for it in the nearest library.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.96,0:06:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some people are willing to die for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.06,0:06:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But generationally, it doesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.06,0:06:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So in one generation, it sounds idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.06,0:06:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next generation, it sounds like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that's our rights, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.06,0:06:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our rights, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it depends on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.09,0:06:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.73,0:06:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is just the statement of the content,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.73,0:06:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the field, and the infinite context.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.73,0:07:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a statement in words.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what arises out of this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are the spiritual foundations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual foundations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world in which I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.11,0:07:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,rural Wisconsin, back in the 30s,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.11,0:07:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we considered that there was only two kinds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.11,0:07:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people like this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.11,0:07:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that are on the blackboard here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there were criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There's Machine Gun Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.40,0:07:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then everybody else was like we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.40,0:07:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We just assumed this is the way the world was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.49,0:07:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I never experienced anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.49,0:07:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn't this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We read about them, John Dillinger,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.49,0:07:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Machine Gun Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.49,0:07:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the criminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.49,0:07:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,bank robber weirdo types,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonnie and Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was the normal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what we thought were normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.00,0:07:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this thing work?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look in this thing, you go blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.07,0:08:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't know how you make it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.07,0:08:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, does this thing work?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.68,0:08:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I pushed the yellow button.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.06,0:08:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I just changed the channel. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.06,0:08:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was friendly, polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.57,0:08:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you owe people money,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.57,0:08:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you paid them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.57,0:08:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody was moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was helpful, kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.57,0:08:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You could drop into any neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.57,0:08:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,knock on the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'd say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.57,0:08:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.57,0:08:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.63,0:08:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody acted in a respectable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.63,0:08:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and honorable fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.66,0:08:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody acted friendly, orderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.66,0:08:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no riots anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.66,0:08:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was expected to be sane
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.89,0:08:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and act sane.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.89,0:08:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you weren't sane,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.30,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you got quickly told about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.30,0:08:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody tried to be fair,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.30,0:08:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,ethical, and balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.37,0:08:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You tried to have a sense of humor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.37,0:08:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,take things lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.37,0:09:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was humane.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.37,0:09:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anybody that was cruel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.40,0:09:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or willfully cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.40,0:09:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If some animal was suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried to put it to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so it wouldn't suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.94,0:09:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was sort of happy to be alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.94,0:09:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,People were relatively modest,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.01,0:09:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.18,0:09:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Life was pretty easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there were the criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.75,0:09:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, there were only two kinds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Machine gun Kelly,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.94,0:09:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then us, the normal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.23,0:09:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't think there was anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.23,0:09:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We call that now
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.36,0:09:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.58,0:09:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I like the scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.58,0:09:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the boy scouts, the girl scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.58,0:09:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because they all take you right over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They all take you right over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.44,0:10:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes you to a moral kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,moral reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral and ethical.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about the fact that the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.70,0:10:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is only
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.70,0:10:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,1% of the mind is active.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.70,0:10:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks your mind is 100% active
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.70,0:10:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,except when you're asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.70,0:10:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's reconfirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is only 1% active.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.40,0:10:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.91,0:10:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.49,0:10:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you lying to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.13,0:10:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'all know Susan from all the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.13,0:10:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,video tapes and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.13,0:10:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't be able to do this work
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.13,0:10:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,without Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.13,0:10:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.34,0:10:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Susan, we wouldn't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.18,0:10:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.49,0:10:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that only 1% of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.49,0:10:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually active.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you meditate and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.49,0:10:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I can't get my mind to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.49,0:10:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It just keeps thinking, thinking, thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.49,0:10:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,about the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.71,0:11:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To merely know that 99%
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.71,0:11:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of your mind is silent at all times
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.71,0:11:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a giant step forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.96,0:11:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts arise out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.47,0:11:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thought arises out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.05,0:11:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of non-form.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.30,0:11:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes form.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It arises because of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.30,0:11:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your fascination with thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes form.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.30,0:11:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it dies away in the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.55,0:11:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thought is like a tone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.55,0:11:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,like a note of music.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.74,0:11:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner does it arise
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.74,0:11:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,than it is already fading away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.38,0:11:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.34,0:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to rapidly advance in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.34,0:11:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is you stay on the crest of the wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.34,0:11:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.34,0:11:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of wanting to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.38,0:11:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender it as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Witness it as a phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.38,0:11:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,without any intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.38,0:12:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.85,0:12:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that it's coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of an energy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.70,0:12:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,field that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thrives on the fascination
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.60,0:12:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you give it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.60,0:12:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.33,0:12:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As you surrender it, as it arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.33,0:12:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be like surrendering music.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.33,0:12:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you cling to the phrase
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.33,0:12:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that just passed by,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.33,0:12:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't hear the music that's playing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.36,0:12:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you stay on top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.36,0:12:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness, detach
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.78,0:12:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,from it like you do with music.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.78,0:12:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.29,0:12:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering it as it arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,people who meditate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.99,0:12:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the average mind goes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.72,0:12:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in one of directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.72,0:12:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who are always trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.72,0:12:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipate the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're trying to control the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Control the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.94,0:12:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're living on the front of the wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.94,0:13:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.23,0:13:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to the present reality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.23,0:13:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're already anticipating
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.23,0:13:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the next moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.42,0:13:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are people who live on the back of the wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's happened already
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.46,0:13:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they won't let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.46,0:13:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still chewing it all over,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.46,0:13:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,chewing it all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people that are fearful
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.10,0:13:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are always living in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.10,0:13:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,People that are depressed and remorseful
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.10,0:13:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are always clinging and reworking the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.10,0:13:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to deny
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.86,0:13:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the temptation,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the seduction of either one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anticipation of the future
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.54,0:13:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is a seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinging to the past is a seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to refuse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.57,0:13:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the seduction of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.57,0:13:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead live right on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.57,0:13:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the crest of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.57,0:13:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live on the crest of the moment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.57,0:13:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with absolutely, absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,no resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.37,0:13:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to that which is being experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.40,0:13:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you can go through surgery without anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.33,0:14:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done it twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.62,0:14:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you begin to resist the pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.62,0:14:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.78,0:14:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.78,0:14:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being chopped up, fully awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.26,0:14:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by staying on the crest of the wave,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.26,0:14:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you can actually have anesthesia
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.26,0:14:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that can saw off your thumb
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and even feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.74,0:14:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you're in a beatific state
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.74,0:14:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you let go like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.74,0:14:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to transcend the ego altogether
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.74,0:14:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're like uplifted by the angelic,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.74,0:14:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,uplifted in the angelic kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.86,0:14:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In a state of exquisite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.50,0:14:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what the mind does
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.50,0:14:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to hang on to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.50,0:14:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind then has like a mind of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.50,0:14:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It has its own motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.85,0:14:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to politicize everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.85,0:14:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to finish a book now
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.85,0:14:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the difficulty is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.85,0:14:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.85,0:15:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody's out there politicizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.68,0:15:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's practically impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.68,0:15:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a neutral statement in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.68,0:15:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.41,0:15:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody has already positionalized it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.41,0:15:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and politicized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.41,0:15:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.28,0:15:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind likes to moralize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.28,0:15:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to idealize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.28,0:15:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It hypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.28,0:15:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to say what if.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.75,0:15:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there is no answer to the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.75,0:15:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical itself calibrates it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.75,0:15:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.90,0:15:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.90,0:15:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an attempt to manipulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.90,0:15:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.03,0:15:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not the same as the alternative.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.03,0:15:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's alternative possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.03,0:15:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But the hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.03,0:15:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of refuting an argument
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't want to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by manufacturing intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,construction
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.03,0:15:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that would invalidate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.03,0:15:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind hypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.19,0:16:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to romanticize.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How much does
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.99,0:16:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so much that it calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.99,0:16:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as less than 200
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.99,0:16:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,not true, invalid,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.99,0:16:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, quite invalid,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.99,0:16:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,gain such a hold?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.70,0:16:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we romanticize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Romanticize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.26,0:16:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We join the parade,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.26,0:16:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.74,0:16:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,workmen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.74,0:16:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you have nothing to lose but your chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.78,0:16:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to lose but your chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.78,0:16:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You got your life to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.13,0:16:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That costs 100 million people too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.13,0:16:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They died on communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.19,0:16:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They died.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.51,0:16:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Died by the millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.51,0:16:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.51,0:16:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They died by the millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not such minor little intellectual niceties
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.44,0:16:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but quite a dramatic reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.79,0:16:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Romanticize.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.79,0:16:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So we romanticize the fallacious
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.27,0:17:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Third Reich.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.27,0:17:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Fuhrer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.97,0:17:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Romanticize the Fuhrer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Romanticize Deutschland über alles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.93,0:17:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Romanticize the workmen
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.93,0:17:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,against the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.93,0:17:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We get out there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the barricades,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I don't go to peace parades
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.96,0:17:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is they're too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.96,0:17:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All that romanticizing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.38,0:17:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.44,0:17:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we criticize,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we dramatize,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.44,0:17:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophize, victimize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.44,0:17:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The victimology is the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.44,0:17:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,growing industry
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.44,0:17:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.18,0:17:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Victimize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.71,0:17:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Child Lawyers Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.71,0:17:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.38,0:17:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So projecting perpetrator victim
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.38,0:17:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is highly profitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.51,0:17:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.51,0:18:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,easy to romanticize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.51,0:18:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Get people emotionalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.54,0:18:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Rationalize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind likes to intellectualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentalize, glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to demonize.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what would you do without demons?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.02,0:18:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't write a newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.02,0:18:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,without a demon out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Congressman so-and-so is today's demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a new demon out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we prize having demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.66,0:18:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind likes to theorize.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.66,0:18:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So this little 1%
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,keeps going because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.88,0:18:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the energy we give it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're not the victim of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.88,0:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one that's giving it the energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.88,0:18:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.23,0:18:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at your mind right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.23,0:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find it's silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm listening to everybody's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.99,0:18:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hear anything out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.99,0:18:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's thinking at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.08,0:18:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You find that underneath the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.58,0:19:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what you think is thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.58,0:19:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.58,0:19:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not thinking at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So where do you find the silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.19,0:19:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't find the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.19,0:19:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,between the billiard balls,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.19,0:19:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A, B, C.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.19,0:19:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Try and hold these two billiard balls apart
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.19,0:19:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the infinite between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.48,0:19:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.48,0:19:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're like flying fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.48,0:19:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thought is arising out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.92,0:19:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the sea, this flying fish arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Or another flying fish arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.14,0:19:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in some...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.59,0:19:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.59,0:19:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The flying fish are coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They flop on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.87,0:19:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is arising of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's causing them to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.54,0:19:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The human intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.34,0:19:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,res interna.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.53,0:19:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sees a fish come up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.53,0:19:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a fish come up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.53,0:19:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a fish come up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:20:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says, see, they're making triangles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.73,0:20:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of millions of people
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.89,0:20:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.89,0:20:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't see through that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.66,0:20:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't see through that fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The fish are not making triangles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.54,0:20:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.54,0:20:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Your stupid mind is making triangles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.54,0:20:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy's not out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.50,0:20:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you can't destroy the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.50,0:20:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is you're looking 180 degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,out of phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.01,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the infatuation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with this inner phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.07,0:20:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pleasure we get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.07,0:20:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.07,0:20:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.35,0:20:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not based in reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how does it keep on going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.35,0:20:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the animal illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.28,0:20:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to get in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.28,0:20:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have the juice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.95,0:21:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ego gets out of negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.95,0:21:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, my mind doesn't enjoy suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.95,0:21:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.27,0:21:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.27,0:21:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody loves to feel victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.17,0:21:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They love to feel anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.58,0:21:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.58,0:21:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the animal is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.16,0:21:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you out there that are psychotherapists,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.16,0:21:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know how hard it is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.16,0:21:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to get anybody out of victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.22,0:21:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.22,0:21:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They hate you for trying to get them out of victimhood
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.22,0:21:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because the payoff is enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.22,0:21:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be the hero, the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.22,0:21:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.22,0:21:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.22,0:21:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to sue people.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.26,0:21:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to feel sorry for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.26,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to get people out of victimhood
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.26,0:21:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is almost an impossible job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.26,0:21:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember some patients,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.26,0:21:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can see the enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.26,0:21:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, you're the star of the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.35,0:21:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.34,0:22:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dualistic perpetrator-victim model
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.79,0:22:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,pays off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.79,0:22:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And unconsciously,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.56,0:22:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.56,0:22:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which keeps the ego going.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.20,0:22:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, what keeps the ego going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.20,0:22:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy is derived from
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.20,0:22:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.20,0:22:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal energy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.20,0:22:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of those energy fuels
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.20,0:22:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.36,0:22:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what keeps the ego going.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.71,0:22:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The payoff of being righteous,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.71,0:22:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.02,0:22:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.02,0:22:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord, look what they do to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.02,0:22:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People make God wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.02,0:22:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.02,0:22:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego gets such satisfaction out of it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.02,0:22:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that it goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.02,0:22:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.02,0:22:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.50,0:22:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as we see here,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.50,0:22:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,truth then,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.70,0:22:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts are rising out about unity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.70,0:22:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and appear as
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:22:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,separateness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.11,0:23:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we're talking now,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.11,0:23:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as we're talking now,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.18,0:23:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind, there's no mind
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.18,0:23:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that's talking in this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.18,0:23:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,up here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.18,0:23:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.24,0:23:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This talking is going on of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.24,0:23:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no idea what's going to be said
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.24,0:23:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,until I hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.24,0:23:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what's going to be said?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.78,0:23:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.00,0:23:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, what are you going to talk about tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.00,0:23:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what I'm going to talk about tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.00,0:23:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the slightest idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.00,0:23:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We make up something
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.00,0:23:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make them happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.03,0:23:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.43,0:23:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to speak and so and so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.43,0:23:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.53,0:23:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not going to be satisfied with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.85,0:23:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is having the slightest idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.85,0:23:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.54,0:23:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you can make a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.96,0:24:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,generality, but there's no knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.06,0:24:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,once the mind goes silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.06,0:24:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't speak again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.06,0:24:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Speakingness happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.06,0:24:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spontaneous event.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.06,0:24:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the interaction of the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.60,0:24:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would say that aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.60,0:24:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jung called the persona,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.60,0:24:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the interaction-ness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.60,0:24:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with the social world,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.60,0:24:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with the beingness inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.98,0:24:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So it serves
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.98,0:24:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a communication function.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.98,0:24:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But it happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.98,0:24:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.98,0:24:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,See what the hand did there?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.05,0:24:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what it did to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.78,0:24:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It did it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.30,0:24:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who knows what it's going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.23,0:24:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.30,0:24:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't subscribe to the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.58,0:24:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It can say and do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.90,0:24:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's totally insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.99,0:25:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Unreliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.62,0:25:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We get by in spite of the mind, not because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.62,0:25:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know why you survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.62,0:25:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind says, oh, without me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.62,0:25:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.62,0:25:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What keeps you alive
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.94,0:25:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.94,0:25:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.07,0:25:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you survive
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.26,0:25:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in spite of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.03,0:25:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, I wouldn't remember my vitamins
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.03,0:25:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.03,0:25:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.03,0:25:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that made your ego remember the vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.03,0:25:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.03,0:25:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the energy of life itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.03,0:25:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind wouldn't even
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.22,0:25:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,think of the vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.22,0:25:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we survive
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.11,0:25:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.11,0:25:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and in spite of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.11,0:25:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego would like you to think that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.11,0:25:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,without it, you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.85,0:25:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.85,0:25:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I practiced for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.46,0:26:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.17,0:26:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I'm dying
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.42,0:26:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm taking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.42,0:26:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.81,0:26:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, well, then you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.81,0:26:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.50,0:26:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What if this area doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.36,0:26:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that sounds awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.35,0:26:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us are going to be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.35,0:26:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.00,0:26:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.00,0:26:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As you'll see later on from some charts,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.00,0:26:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we swoop in here together,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.00,0:26:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,settle out generally
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.03,0:26:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in sort of the same area,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.03,0:26:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then karmically we evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.03,0:26:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all swoop back, maybe in a different place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.03,0:26:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,see?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.10,0:26:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us swoop together.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.10,0:26:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole crowd here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.09,0:26:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all one big swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.09,0:26:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a bunch of herons or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.66,0:27:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us here are one big swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.62,0:27:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We swoop in together all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.62,0:27:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.26,0:27:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're all destined for enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.49,0:27:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.49,0:27:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.49,0:27:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is destined for enlightenment here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.87,0:27:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.87,0:27:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise you wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.87,0:27:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you be at a lecture on enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.87,0:27:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,if you weren't here?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.12,0:27:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The end is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.12,0:27:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The end is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.63,0:27:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that is a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.63,0:27:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The end is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.63,0:27:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we just see how that came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.63,0:27:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're rerunning sort of how did I ever get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.70,0:27:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like I did with you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.86,0:27:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to tell you how it all came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.30,0:27:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we have to stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.30,0:27:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hate to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.24,0:27:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just getting into it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.24,0:27:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,12.30 we stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.24,0:27:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.24,0:27:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, the lower mind and higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.59,0:28:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can stop now?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.28,0:28:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.72,0:28:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What, are you against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.93,0:28:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how she's against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.93,0:28:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.26,0:28:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.27,0:28:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She's probably an enemy of some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.27,0:28:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We can project anything we want to onto anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.17,0:28:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.17,0:28:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How we want to see it, we can project it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.17,0:28:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we react to it as though it is that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.62,0:28:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand that that which is of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.62,0:28:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is only of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.68,0:28:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That which exists in reality
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.68,0:28:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,exists independently of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.74,0:28:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.82,0:28:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, no, I don't want anybody to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.82,0:28:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,anything during lunchtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.46,0:28:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What time are we due back?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.38,0:29:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What time?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.46,0:29:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We're due back at 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.49,0:29:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.49,0:29:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you only have an hour and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.26,0:29:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you don't have to think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.26,0:29:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're going to think that you're thinking about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.22,0:29:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.22,0:29:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.22,0:29:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.22,0:29:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.08,0:29:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.08,0:29:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.11,0:29:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, identify with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.11,0:29:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The field in which everything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.11,0:29:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.11,0:29:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you move from ego to spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.11,0:29:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because spirit is the ultimate context.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.11,0:29:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're the context,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.11,0:29:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,not the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.78,0:29:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Bravo. Thank you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.96,0:29:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're wired up for action.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.96,0:29:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, boy, look how loud that volume is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.96,0:29:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be Goethe
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.08,0:29:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.62,0:30:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.10,0:30:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody can hear well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.00,0:30:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems I can hear very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.00,0:30:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where my mouth is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.09,0:30:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.47,0:30:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Next generation, everybody will be born with these.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.78,0:30:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean? You're born with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.78,0:30:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We were tracking...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.97,0:30:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.97,0:30:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.97,0:30:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're trying
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.13,0:30:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to recontextualize mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.13,0:30:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We got through
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.26,0:30:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, how it evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.26,0:30:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,since the beginning of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.26,0:30:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of having a pejorative attitude towards it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.26,0:30:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we accept that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.26,0:30:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,its function, its value
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.26,0:30:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is to keep you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.32,0:30:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego feels that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.32,0:30:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,unless it gets things,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.32,0:30:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.32,0:30:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's serving its function.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.32,0:30:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we say you're greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.32,0:30:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you get, you want more.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.32,0:30:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.32,0:30:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.32,0:31:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you have, you want more.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.32,0:31:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.32,0:31:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.82,0:31:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the illusion is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.82,0:31:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's how you stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.82,0:31:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you surrender to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.82,0:31:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the field. Not to the content
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.82,0:31:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field, which is the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.82,0:31:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.82,0:31:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dominion of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.82,0:31:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the field, the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.02,0:31:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That if you're doing the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.14,0:31:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,course of miracles, it says
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.14,0:31:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can walk out into the world with no money,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.14,0:31:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,no food, and somehow you will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.14,0:31:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.14,0:31:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No money,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.81,0:31:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,no food, no nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.38,0:31:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, yeah, it's spirit's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.38,0:31:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,worry. Why should I worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.42,0:31:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure enough, you're wandering through town
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.42,0:31:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.42,0:31:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,says, I can't eat my whole lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.42,0:31:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you eat this sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.42,0:31:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything just happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.15,0:31:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.15,0:31:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, it has ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.15,0:32:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.70,0:32:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.73,0:32:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only thing you have to see
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.73,0:32:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is that everything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.73,0:32:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically, spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.73,0:32:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.56,0:32:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you make the decision
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.56,0:32:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to be deliberate,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.56,0:32:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that decision was spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.65,0:32:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that irresponsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.90,0:32:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Terrific!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.96,0:32:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it's irresponsible. I love being irresponsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.96,0:32:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.96,0:32:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for anything I say or do.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.18,0:32:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's God's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.18,0:32:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is occurring spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.33,0:32:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically, as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.33,0:32:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.33,0:32:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is nothing but
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.78,0:32:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality coming into
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.78,0:32:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.87,0:32:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the wordingness of a talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.87,0:32:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,such as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.87,0:32:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.87,0:32:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,coming into actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.87,0:33:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.87,0:33:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, you're the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.94,0:33:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you hear is what you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.94,0:33:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,collectively bring forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.98,0:33:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hear is what the field brings forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.98,0:33:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.72,0:33:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.72,0:33:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically, as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.72,0:33:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.75,0:33:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a collective intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.75,0:33:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This speakingness happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.61,0:33:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.50,0:33:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we were talking about mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.50,0:33:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that mind evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.50,0:33:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You have this animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.50,0:33:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you give him a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.50,0:33:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, he's a rather primitive animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.50,0:33:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.14,0:33:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but in a sort of rudimentary fashion,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.14,0:33:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,still with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.14,0:33:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.14,0:33:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,dominating the thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.66,0:33:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,People arrive at conclusions
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.66,0:33:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that they want to arrive at.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.82,0:33:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than following the conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.82,0:33:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the dialectic
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.42,0:34:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.71,0:34:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are many people in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.71,0:34:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to whom four and four does not create,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.71,0:34:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, a total eight,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.71,0:34:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't want it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.48,0:34:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They run for office all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.71,0:34:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you that are into esoteric,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.71,0:34:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.71,0:34:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,know that there's two energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.71,0:34:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,one called higher mind and one lower mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.71,0:34:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So lower mind thinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.71,0:34:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.71,0:34:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it has not heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.78,0:34:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the dialectic
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.94,0:34:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.94,0:34:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So it ignores reason
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.94,0:34:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and it speaks about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.94,0:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what it likes and what it feels like
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.94,0:34:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.94,0:34:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what is provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.94,0:34:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So it hasn't quite reached
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.94,0:34:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated level of the 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.94,0:34:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see lower mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.94,0:34:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a pointer somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.94,0:34:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody stole it, give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.18,0:35:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see lower mind at 155,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.18,0:35:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is run by desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.28,0:35:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It still wants control.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.28,0:35:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It tends to be literal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.34,0:35:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's ego dominated.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.34,0:35:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It tends to exploit life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.34,0:35:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is using reason
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.34,0:35:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.34,0:35:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,an animal kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.34,0:35:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.54,0:35:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher mind is more interested
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.54,0:35:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in value
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.70,0:35:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.70,0:35:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It tends to be inclusive
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.70,0:35:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.70,0:35:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.05,0:35:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of the survival
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.05,0:35:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of others instead of just
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.05,0:35:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.30,0:35:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It tends to be creative,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.82,0:35:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,cooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.52,0:35:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sophisticated, informed,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.52,0:35:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.52,0:35:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks in terms of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.52,0:35:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms of balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.68,0:35:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees itself as
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.68,0:35:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,serving life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.68,0:35:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.68,0:35:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks at context instead of content.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.68,0:36:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks at context
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.68,0:36:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of content.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.68,0:36:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So to move forward in consciousness then,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.68,0:36:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you move to identification
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.68,0:36:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.68,0:36:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The field rather than the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.68,0:36:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you move to the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.68,0:36:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the content will take care of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.68,0:36:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The content will take care of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.78,0:36:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,During the break I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.89,0:36:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,gosh, there's no chair here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.11,0:36:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.11,0:36:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,two people came over and dragged over chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.11,0:36:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.14,0:36:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say bring over a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.72,0:36:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you become
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.72,0:36:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then, what you become
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.72,0:36:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.72,0:36:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.83,0:36:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.83,0:36:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.44,0:36:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.44,0:36:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.44,0:36:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you choose,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.98,0:36:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you value
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.98,0:36:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then determines
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.98,0:36:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what falls into your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.98,0:37:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's nothing to blame
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.98,0:37:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if there's no cause
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.98,0:37:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's no effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.34,0:37:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What you witness and experience
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.34,0:37:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is a field, an impersonal effect
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.34,0:37:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.34,0:37:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Impersonal effect of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.77,0:37:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When you choose
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.12,0:37:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,goodwill
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.11,0:37:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,towards everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.43,0:37:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when you choose
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.62,0:37:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to support life in all of its expressions,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.62,0:37:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when you choose
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.14,0:37:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the exquisite
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.14,0:37:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty of all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.30,0:37:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when you choose to see
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.30,0:37:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the sacredness of all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.39,0:37:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your life automatically changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.39,0:37:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Through that choice
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.12,0:37:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're walking along
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.50,0:37:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the sidewalk and suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.50,0:37:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're struck by the incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.50,0:37:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty of a weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.98,0:37:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see a weed for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.98,0:38:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an exquisite
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.98,0:38:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection of sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.98,0:38:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.30,0:38:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at any weed and you'll see
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.30,0:38:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,its extreme beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.66,0:38:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people can't see it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.72,0:38:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you chip it out of stone
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.72,0:38:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it in a park.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.72,0:38:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.72,0:38:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to make it really big
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.75,0:38:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and overwhelming to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.75,0:38:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.17,0:38:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at all times,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.17,0:38:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,under all circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.17,0:38:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,each thing is exquisitely
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.17,0:38:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfect expression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.17,0:38:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.17,0:38:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.62,0:38:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In the dance of Shiva,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.62,0:38:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,each thing is exquisitely,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.62,0:38:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly, and perfectly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.62,0:38:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.02,0:38:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is the perfect expression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.02,0:39:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it has become.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.56,0:39:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arises
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.56,0:39:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.56,0:39:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.36,0:39:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what do I have to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.16,0:39:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You only have to just
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.16,0:39:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,be what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.16,0:39:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the fulfillment,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.16,0:39:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.29,0:39:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arises
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.29,0:39:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of the joy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.29,0:39:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.42,0:39:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy of one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.83,0:39:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.83,0:39:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.31,0:39:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.31,0:39:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We see as it moved up to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.31,0:39:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the prefrontal cortex is growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.31,0:39:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw how it started out
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.31,0:39:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.31,0:39:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,grew over the millennia,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.31,0:39:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved into brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.31,0:39:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.31,0:39:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how the mind began to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.31,0:39:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in higher and higher
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.31,0:39:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.31,0:39:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from lower mind to higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.86,0:39:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.18,0:40:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.50,0:40:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The social disparities in our world
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.50,0:40:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do really with the predominance
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the voice of lower mind
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.50,0:40:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,versus the voice of higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.13,0:40:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,People bemoan the divisiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.74,0:40:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of current social
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.74,0:40:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,discord
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.74,0:40:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.74,0:40:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's generally between
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.74,0:40:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,lower mind and higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.74,0:40:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you calibrate it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.74,0:40:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,using kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.74,0:40:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that the disparate voices
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.93,0:40:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are really the speakingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.28,0:40:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of lower mind versus
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.28,0:40:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the speakingness of higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.28,0:40:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.28,0:40:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like two societies
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.28,0:40:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,together.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.21,0:40:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is kinesiologic
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.26,0:40:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,response.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.26,0:40:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.26,0:40:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is looked at through quantum
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.26,0:40:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.97,0:40:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinesiologic response,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.97,0:40:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the condition of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.97,0:41:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is calculated
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.10,0:41:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Schrodinger equations
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.10,0:41:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which are both
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.10,0:41:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,time dependent and time independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.10,0:41:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Schrodinger equations
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.10,0:41:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which are mathematical,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.10,0:41:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and I save you the problem of putting them up there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.45,0:41:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,then the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.45,0:41:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is so overwhelmingly important
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.45,0:41:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because they introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.45,0:41:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of consciousness and intention
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.45,0:41:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.45,0:41:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,then collapses the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.45,0:41:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as the actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.45,0:41:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you have a new state of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.45,0:41:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,different total state
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.80,0:41:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.63,0:41:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnosable mathematically
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.53,0:41:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Dirac equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.53,0:41:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Schrodinger equations
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.53,0:41:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Heisenberg principle collapses
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.53,0:41:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the wave function, which you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.53,0:41:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,calculate now
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.53,0:41:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Dirac equations
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.53,0:41:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that's called the von Neumann process
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.53,0:41:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and you now have a new state
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.53,0:41:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.53,0:41:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a new potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.23,0:42:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so every decision, every intention
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.23,0:42:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,moment to moment
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.18,0:42:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand what it's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.78,0:42:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Heisenberg principle is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.78,0:42:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the introduction of the freedom of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.78,0:42:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.78,0:42:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free to choose
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.91,0:42:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the available options.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.91,0:42:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The options of course are limited
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.91,0:42:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.81,0:42:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At this level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.81,0:42:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,these are your options,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.81,0:42:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at this level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.34,0:42:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,these are your options,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.78,0:42:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,these are your choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.78,0:42:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The value of quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.78,0:42:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is we can go from logic and reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.91,0:42:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.91,0:42:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we can move on to quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.74,0:42:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we can move on to non-linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.74,0:42:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and we eventually come
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.74,0:42:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to the level of the 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.74,0:42:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,where you enter a new paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.74,0:42:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality determined by
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.74,0:42:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.38,0:42:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual reality begins
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.38,0:43:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,classically at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.38,0:43:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the energy field of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.38,0:43:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Love changes the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.38,0:43:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the value of everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.38,0:43:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence itself
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.61,0:43:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that we value.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.86,0:43:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you that are interested
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.86,0:43:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in this process
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.86,0:43:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you look up on the internet
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.86,0:43:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Stapp,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.86,0:43:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of advanced theoretical physics
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.30,0:43:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at Berkeley
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.30,0:43:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who explains the von Neumann process
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.30,0:43:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and process one, process two.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.30,0:43:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the purpose of all this
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.36,0:43:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you can move from reason
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.36,0:43:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and logic, the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.36,0:43:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,without becoming illogical
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.36,0:43:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or unreasonable
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.36,0:43:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as you move into spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.62,0:43:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.06,0:43:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,doing intellectual pride
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.06,0:43:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to admit they're interested
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.06,0:43:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual realities
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.70,0:43:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they say all that uh-oh stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.70,0:43:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,woo-woo stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.60,0:43:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a guy who used to run a clinic
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.60,0:44:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,back in Arizona
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.60,0:44:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and he said
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.60,0:44:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,woo-woo,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.39,0:44:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,means you pass beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.39,0:44:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what is reasonable, logical
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.39,0:44:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and comprehensible through the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.39,0:44:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm showing you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.39,0:44:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to move what is beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.39,0:44:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or incomprehensible through the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.39,0:44:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you can move right through the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.39,0:44:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics, non-linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.39,0:44:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and move right into a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.39,0:44:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So at 500 what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.71,0:44:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is the mind makes a paradigm jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.93,0:44:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Eisen, Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.93,0:44:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and Freud,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.25,0:44:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1999
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.07,0:44:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's a paradigm jump
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.07,0:44:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a paradigm jump
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.20,0:44:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,if you go to all the conferences
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.20,0:44:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.20,0:44:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,science and consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.20,0:44:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find they all calibrate around 440, 450
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.20,0:44:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they're hanging onto
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.23,0:44:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.23,0:45:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and looking for God in the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.23,0:45:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't find God in the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.23,0:45:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can spend
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.78,0:45:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of dollars in research
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.78,0:45:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,on neurologic functioning
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.87,0:45:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.87,0:45:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that will fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.97,0:45:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.97,0:45:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you calibrate that research in advance
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.97,0:45:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find it calibrates at 140
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.97,0:45:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you what the research is going to show in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.42,0:45:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So one value of calibrating levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.42,0:45:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is you can tell whether an experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.42,0:45:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or a research project
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.42,0:45:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is worth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.58,0:45:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,energizing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.11,0:45:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.58,0:45:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick's research
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.96,0:45:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that discovered the double helix
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.62,0:45:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.62,0:45:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.64,0:45:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He was surprised jointly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.06,0:45:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The last research project
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.15,0:45:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,before he left
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.15,0:45:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was to set up
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.44,0:46:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to research
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.44,0:46:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,neurologic functioning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.44,0:46:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and find the source of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.44,0:46:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,within the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.44,0:46:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,neuroanatomy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.44,0:46:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with neurological functioning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.63,0:46:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that calibrated at 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.17,0:46:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick's stated purpose was
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.17,0:46:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that after we finish this research
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.71,0:46:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.71,0:46:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,man will not believe in life after death
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.71,0:46:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.78,0:46:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And he had great hopes that this project
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.78,0:46:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrated at 140
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.78,0:46:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and cost all of us taxpayers good money
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.90,0:46:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at 140
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.90,0:46:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell it's going to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.06,0:46:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well he saved himself the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.29,0:46:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He left.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.47,0:46:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick died a little while ago
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.47,0:46:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've already asked Crick
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.20,0:46:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I have Crick's permission
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.49,0:46:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that he is very very
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.49,0:46:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisitely happy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.90,0:46:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,happy to share the wisdom and the news
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.32,0:46:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's still very much alive
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.32,0:46:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and that there is no death.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.32,0:47:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Crick passed over
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.53,0:47:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and is very happy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.53,0:47:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and excited to find
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.53,0:47:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was dead wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.41,0:47:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Crick
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.63,0:47:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because I understand the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.63,0:47:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was once an atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.63,0:47:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a dedicated atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.08,0:47:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a deadly atheist boy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.08,0:47:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who got in conversation with me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.08,0:47:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because I had a high IQ
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.08,0:47:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and a sharp wit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.66,0:47:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I knew all about theology
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.66,0:47:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and epistemology and ontology
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.66,0:47:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway I'm a great friend of Crick's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.66,0:47:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and Watts and both
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.66,0:47:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I understand exactly how Crick felt
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.66,0:47:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can sympathize with him
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.66,0:47:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what a preposterous
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.69,0:47:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy that there is an eternal soul
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.69,0:47:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can understand him
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.69,0:47:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just get a kick that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.17,0:47:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got a sense of humor
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.17,0:47:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's happy to share with the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.17,0:47:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and we always get his permission about this
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.49,0:48:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.71,0:48:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so we'll move on to the next thing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.35,0:48:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,uh
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.48,0:48:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this is just comparing the two paradigms of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.48,0:48:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the newtonium
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.48,0:48:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the quantum
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.48,0:48:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in the newtonium
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.74,0:48:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is fixed and determined and limited
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.74,0:48:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.74,0:48:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is really a way
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.74,0:48:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really force
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.34,0:48:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when you move into quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.34,0:48:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that there's simultaneity
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.34,0:48:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you see there's non predictability
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.34,0:48:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that anything can happen anytime
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.34,0:48:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what I mean
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.34,0:48:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anything can happen anytime
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.34,0:48:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anything can happen anytime
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.34,0:48:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anything can happen anytime
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.34,0:48:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can end up bambling
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.34,0:48:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in a newtonian lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.10,0:48:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,no such thing would happen
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.10,0:48:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,everything has to be logical reasonable
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.10,0:48:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,sequential
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.99,0:48:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we can just go totally mad
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.99,0:48:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody gets it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.47,0:48:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,unruly
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.47,0:49:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,disorderly unpredictable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.47,0:49:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.47,0:49:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,unlimited
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.30,0:49:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so the newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.26,0:49:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm is provable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.26,0:49:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and measurable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.26,0:49:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the closer we get to reality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.26,0:49:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unpredictable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.82,0:49:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's subject to imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.82,0:49:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so we'll move to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.14,0:49:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're moving from the limitation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.14,0:49:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of the newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.14,0:49:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we're moving to non linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.14,0:49:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.17,0:49:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see the opening
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.17,0:49:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of a new paradigm of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.17,0:49:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to leave reason
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.17,0:49:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.17,0:49:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,all along the way
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.03,0:49:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so people won't think you're one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.03,0:49:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,woo-woos
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.91,0:49:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mind thinks dualistically
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.91,0:49:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a this causing a that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.10,0:49:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a this causing a that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.47,0:50:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a this causing a that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.79,0:50:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it divides everything into a duality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.43,0:50:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it divides everything into a duality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.43,0:50:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we pointed out
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.43,0:50:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the disaster
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.43,0:50:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a consequence of the marxian
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.43,0:50:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,dualistic perpetrator victim duality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.43,0:50:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,however
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.43,0:50:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.52,0:50:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to think dualistically
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.52,0:50:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.55,0:50:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,let's take two seeming opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.55,0:50:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,let's take goodness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.55,0:50:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and badness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.19,0:50:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that there are not two
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.19,0:50:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,different things at all
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.19,0:50:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.19,0:50:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,desirability
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.22,0:50:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if desirability is present
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.22,0:50:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we call it good
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.22,0:50:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if desirability is not there
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.22,0:50:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we call it bad
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.29,0:50:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there's not good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.29,0:50:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only desirability
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.18,0:50:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's not two variables
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.37,0:50:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in duality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.37,0:50:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,let's take light and darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.04,0:51:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,light and darkness are certainly opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.04,0:51:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are they not
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.10,0:51:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,no there's only one variable
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.10,0:51:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,light
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.10,0:51:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,light is either present or not present
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.51,0:51:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the same with truth and falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.51,0:51:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of seeing this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.51,0:51:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is truth is either present or not present
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.67,0:51:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there's not an opposite reality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.67,0:51:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,called falseness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.99,0:51:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there's not an opposite reality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.99,0:51:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,light is either present or not present
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.99,0:51:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't have two
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.63,0:51:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions light and dark
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.63,0:51:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you only have one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.92,0:51:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,light is either present or not present
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.92,0:51:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so you only have a matter of degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.92,0:51:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of a single variable
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.92,0:51:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,single variable
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.11,0:51:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind is dualistic
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.11,0:51:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,things in terms of opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.04,0:51:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending the duality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.20,0:51:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the polarity of the opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.20,0:51:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the barriers
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.42,0:51:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.48,0:51:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,guarded by the two dragons
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.48,0:51:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,classically
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.82,0:52:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the doorways to truth
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.82,0:52:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,guarded by two dragons
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.82,0:52:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then we'll move to the next one
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.00,0:52:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you have goodness and badness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.00,0:52:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,light
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.13,0:52:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have hot and cold
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.13,0:52:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,surely you say hot and cold are opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.22,0:52:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,no heat is either present or not
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.22,0:52:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's present to a high degree
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.22,0:52:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we call it hot
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.22,0:52:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's absent we call it cold
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.22,0:52:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not two opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.22,0:52:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only one variable
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.22,0:52:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence or the absence of heat
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.56,0:52:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.75,0:52:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,desirability
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.75,0:52:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we say one thing is more valuable than another
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.36,0:52:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we were someplace or other
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.81,0:52:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what was it 205 I think
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.81,0:52:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the hope diamond calibrates it 205
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.81,0:52:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.87,0:52:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,now if you think it's wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.87,0:52:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,where do we move
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.87,0:52:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,oh it's precious it's valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.87,0:52:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it's worthwhile it's marvelous
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.87,0:52:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's A1
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.97,0:53:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then we say it's not so good
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.06,0:53:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to give me the hope diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.06,0:53:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly I don't want the hope diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.06,0:53:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,would you want the hope diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.06,0:53:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody want the hope diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.38,0:53:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,good people oh there's the one that's going to descend to the top
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.38,0:53:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to die
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.41,0:53:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we all know what goes with the hope diamond don't we
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.41,0:53:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so yeah it calibrated 205
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.41,0:53:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's a nice pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.41,0:53:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,a piece of glass
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.41,0:53:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wouldn't want it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.54,0:53:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,okay so
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.54,0:53:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,some would say it's precious valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.54,0:53:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,worthwhile some people would say
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.54,0:53:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral oh the hope diamond's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.54,0:53:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,okay if you want to give it to me okay
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.54,0:53:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,other people would say no I think it's awful
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.54,0:53:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and other people would say
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.54,0:53:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it brings bad luck and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.54,0:53:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't want the hope diamond so
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.54,0:53:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it has no
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.54,0:53:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic value it only has the value
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.54,0:53:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that we assign to it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.63,0:53:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,most people don't want it wouldn't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.63,0:53:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,take a chance for the hope diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.63,0:53:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want it myself
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.63,0:53:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,see moving on
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.11,0:54:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the progressive fields of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.11,0:54:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we were talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.46,0:54:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to glimpse
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.56,0:54:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that which people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.56,0:54:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,misinterpret that the Buddha said
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.56,0:54:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite reality is between
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.56,0:54:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,two thoughts it's prior to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.56,0:54:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,two thoughts prior not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.56,0:54:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,between the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.52,0:54:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that nobody's ever succeeded in becoming
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.52,0:54:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened by discerning the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.52,0:54:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite reality between thoughts is because
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.52,0:54:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not possible
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.52,0:54:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a good explanation isn't it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.52,0:54:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandth of a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.26,0:54:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,second now
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.29,0:54:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind cannot move that quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.29,0:54:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind cannot move quick enough
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.29,0:54:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what then is able to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.64,0:54:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,discern the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.64,0:54:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.64,0:54:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.93,0:54:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.02,0:54:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is too slow
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.28,0:54:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how intently you focus
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.28,0:54:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the passage of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.28,0:55:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you're never going to get to the space
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.28,0:55:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.76,0:55:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody here ever do that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.76,0:55:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,manage to get to the space between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.98,0:55:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,no never has happened
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.33,0:55:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,not possible
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.77,0:55:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind can't move that quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.77,0:55:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.02,0:55:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what is capable of moving that quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.02,0:55:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.34,0:55:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is trying to catch
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.34,0:55:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,between form
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.10,0:55:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what is faster than one ten thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.10,0:55:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is back here
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.10,0:55:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer witness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.10,0:55:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so you move from identifying
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.26,0:55:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with the content of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.26,0:55:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize you're not the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.26,0:55:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you're that which witnesses the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.26,0:55:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you know you're thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.26,0:55:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,people say I'm thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.26,0:55:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you know you're thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.62,0:55:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe you're lying
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.22,0:55:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,how do I know you're thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.22,0:55:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're conscious and aware
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.22,0:56:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.23,0:56:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,identifying with the content of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.23,0:56:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you become that which
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.23,0:56:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize how do you know what you're thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.23,0:56:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because it registers
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.23,0:56:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,how does it register
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.26,0:56:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.26,0:56:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where in the watcher the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.26,0:56:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,out of awareness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.26,0:56:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so what is faster than
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.26,0:56:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.26,0:56:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is the witness watcher observer
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.36,0:56:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what's faster than
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.36,0:56:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.36,0:56:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this you cannot get faster than
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.36,0:56:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.36,0:56:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,become the field
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.90,0:56:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer witness field
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.03,0:56:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.34,0:56:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how does the witness watcher
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.34,0:56:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencer arise
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.34,0:56:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.08,0:56:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's the presence of the light of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.08,0:56:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,itself
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.37,0:56:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so you move back from identifying
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.37,0:56:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the content of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.46,0:56:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to the witness of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.46,0:57:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the experiencer of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.68,0:57:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer the watcher
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.68,0:57:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer the witness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.60,0:57:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that you are
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.60,0:57:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.02,0:57:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness then is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.02,0:57:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.02,0:57:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.02,0:57:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.72,0:57:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as awareness consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.75,0:57:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.19,0:57:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are not the content
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.19,0:57:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not the content
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.19,0:57:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because the content is always changing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.35,0:57:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not even the witness the watcher
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.45,0:57:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you're something more primary than that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.45,0:57:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you become
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.45,0:57:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.22,0:57:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you will say how should I
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.10,0:58:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how shall I meditate
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.00,0:58:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,well I say don't
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.00,0:58:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,contemplate
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.06,0:58:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,why because when you meditate
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.06,0:58:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to take yourself outside of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.06,0:58:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to go in the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.15,0:58:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and sit cross legged
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.95,0:58:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.24,0:58:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to say smoke incense
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.24,0:58:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,light incense
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.24,0:58:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,play gongs
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.24,0:58:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful music
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.24,0:58:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,get into a woo woo mood
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.24,0:58:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,except when you get up from the woo woo mood
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.24,0:58:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you're right back to the fact that the car won't start
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.24,0:58:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.30,0:58:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so meditation is alright
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.45,0:58:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,if you take yourself out of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.45,0:58:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditate day in and day out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.45,0:58:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,non-stop how long
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.75,0:58:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,forever
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.29,0:58:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when are you going to stop meditating
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.29,0:58:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,never
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.54,0:58:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're willing to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.93,0:58:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no trouble with becoming enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.93,0:59:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,through meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.11,0:59:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in the meantime
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.11,0:59:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what's real
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.98,0:59:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what's real is contemplation
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.98,0:59:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,why because to contemplate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.98,0:59:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.98,0:59:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation you have to take yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.98,0:59:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.33,0:59:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,many people reach states of samadhi
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.33,0:59:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,think they're enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.33,0:59:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,except when you get up and walk around
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.33,0:59:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then the state leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.38,0:59:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that is satori
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.38,0:59:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,those are preliminary glimpses
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.38,0:59:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is not enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.38,0:59:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment condition stays the same
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.38,0:59:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when you open your eyes and walk around
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.74,0:59:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so contemplation
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.74,0:59:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is something you can do all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.74,0:59:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,anytime anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.74,0:59:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.74,0:59:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,contemplation is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.63,0:59:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.91,0:59:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it is simultaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.30,0:59:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.30,0:59:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of a mudra
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.96,1:00:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.96,1:00:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the trouble with meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.92,1:00:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is it tends to be too yang
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.19,1:00:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,realization enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.19,1:00:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about as the absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.19,1:00:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,expression
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.22,1:00:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of yin
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.11,1:00:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so as you reach for enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.11,1:00:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it eludes you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.11,1:00:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll meditate harder and harder
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.11,1:00:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and harder
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.56,1:00:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your legs are going to sleep
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.56,1:00:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,your back is itching
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.78,1:00:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you're living on brown rice
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.78,1:00:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got berry berry
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.30,1:00:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and all kinds of crap
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.30,1:00:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're still not enlightened
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.30,1:00:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you all know
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.52,1:00:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we've all tried it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.52,1:00:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,many a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.52,1:00:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn't be here today
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.55,1:00:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,if we hadn't all tried it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.67,1:00:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,rice and no vitamins
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.93,1:00:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,ended up cramped legs
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.57,1:01:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't get us there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.57,1:01:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's too yang it's too determined
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.57,1:01:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,i think i'll be enlightened
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.57,1:01:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so i'll sit down cross-legged
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.57,1:01:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and breathe real funny
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.57,1:01:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and i'll
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.57,1:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll do all these things
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.57,1:01:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll eat weird food
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.57,1:01:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,crap i'm not enlightened yet
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.57,1:01:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.21,1:01:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll turn up more
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.53,1:01:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that's too hard
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.78,1:01:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.87,1:01:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,no it's because it's easy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.87,1:01:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because it's letting go
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.87,1:01:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because it's surrendering
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.90,1:01:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's allowing
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.90,1:01:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because as it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.06,1:01:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as the experiential
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.42,1:01:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,crests you don't try to cling to it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.42,1:01:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't try to out guess it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.42,1:01:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and reach ahead of it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.42,1:01:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't try to suck the energy out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.42,1:01:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by holding on to it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.67,1:02:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.51,1:02:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you pray
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.10,1:02:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you become that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.54,1:02:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you are the prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.84,1:02:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee oh god
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.32,1:02:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,do i surrender my life
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.75,1:02:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,my beingness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.06,1:02:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and i open myself
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.67,1:02:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to the revelation
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.18,1:02:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the divinity of thy presence
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.18,1:02:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of my existence
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.18,1:02:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,huh
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.46,1:02:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your life becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.05,1:02:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the position
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.75,1:02:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.62,1:03:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the supplication
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.87,1:03:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.87,1:03:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the content of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.90,1:03:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you become one
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.15,1:03:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.41,1:03:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which cannot resist
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.95,1:03:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the mudra of the question
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.24,1:03:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which is being
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.37,1:03:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,asked is the very source
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.37,1:03:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of your existence
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.53,1:03:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.78,1:03:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot refuse
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.56,1:03:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so you understand spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.56,1:03:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as an expression of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.17,1:03:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,being
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.94,1:03:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so i want to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.22,1:03:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.22,1:03:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.22,1:03:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.88,1:04:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.88,1:04:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.81,1:04:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.03,1:04:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.03,1:04:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.12,1:04:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.12,1:04:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.12,1:04:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.23,1:04:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're at the level of the spiritual knight, which I spoke of earlier, both of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.18,1:04:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,us were dangerous because we were the spiritual knight that would stop at nothing, forget
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.26,1:04:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,about death, deadly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.62,1:04:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spiritual knight who's dangerous, dangerous when he gets misled, as we can see
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.39,1:04:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world today.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.76,1:05:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual knight, when let loose, very dangerous animal, very dangerous animal when
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.27,1:05:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,he observes the wrong field.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.29,1:05:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.29,1:05:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you see, starting from meditation then, you can go back to the realization that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.84,1:05:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,one is the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.50,1:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you identify with the field and not the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.89,1:05:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How does this affect brain physiology?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.23,1:05:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that a person who is spiritually...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.51,1:05:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolved, has a different brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.99,1:05:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we stop again?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.99,1:05:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,3.15.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.73,1:05:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.37,1:05:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.37,1:05:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you go over 200, the brain physiology changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.24,1:05:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, we're talking now in the average, in the right-handed person.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.88,1:05:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 then, we are primarily left brain animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.20,1:06:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's interesting, you see, is in the animal, the input, the sensory input.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.12,1:06:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes via the thalamus, a fast track, to the amygdala, which is the emotional center.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.96,1:06:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the experience is stored in the memory, which is the hippocampus, right south of Cincinnati
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.34,1:06:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.24,1:06:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The left brain then, below consciousness level 200, is primarily animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.50,1:06:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The fast track is to the emotional center.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.49,1:06:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the slow track is to the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.49,1:06:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.12,1:06:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal brain has dominated for millions and millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.32,1:06:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you plaster on a prefrontal cortex, but it's still in the habit of responding emotionally.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.09,1:06:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jane, you see him?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.18,1:06:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks very dangerous to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.62,1:07:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's call the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.18,1:07:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.50,1:07:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the cortex gets its input, but you see that it's slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.11,1:07:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the left brain, person reacts.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.91,1:07:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It reacts primarily emotionally, what I want, what I don't want, what I like.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.32,1:07:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason only comes in belatedly, belatedly.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.08,1:07:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the left brain dominance then, below consciousness level 200, is linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.07,1:07:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's prone to stress, release of adrenaline, cannons, fight or flight, Selye's stress syndrome.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.29,1:07:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's constantly in a state of stress, it suppresses the thalamus.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.88,1:07:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thalamus output of killer cells.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.84,1:07:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a greater proneness to disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.90,1:07:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It blows out the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.66,1:07:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you go into fight or flight, the acupuncture system goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.78,1:08:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That blows the energy flow to whatever meridian you're blowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.22,1:08:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it's hatred, you're constantly blowing the heart meridian.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.82,1:08:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you get a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.74,1:08:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the left brain then is thymic stress.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.92,1:08:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.96,1:08:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.48,1:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.00,1:08:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases neurotransmitters and eventually depletes your serotonin.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.56,1:08:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Track to the emotions is twice as fast as through the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.46,1:08:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, less than 200 responds first on the animal level.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.01,1:08:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.01,1:08:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.01,1:08:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.01,1:08:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I fear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.04,1:08:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to be on guard against it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.32,1:08:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200 now, the brain physiology changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.72,1:08:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It shifts more to right brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.08,1:09:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference is above 200, the fast track is to the cerebral cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.74,1:09:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 200, we have an amazing development for the first time in evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.32,1:09:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the development of spiritual energy, so-called kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.46,1:09:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200, you get the production of kundalini energy, spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.81,1:09:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important thing is it creates an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.30,1:09:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.30,1:09:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.18,1:09:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level 200 and up, there's the development of the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.68,1:09:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.68,1:09:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.20,1:09:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, over 200 then, now things are processed differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.52,1:09:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The fast track is through the etheric brain and the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.92,1:09:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Very fast to the emotional center.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.82,1:09:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have right brain dominance, which is nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.52,1:09:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What you read is the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.52,1:09:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to read the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.48,1:09:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is at peace because you're released from the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.60,1:09:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is at peace because you're released from the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.60,1:09:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is at peace because you're released from the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.60,1:10:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're releasing endorphins instead of adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.91,1:10:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotions are positive instead of negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.58,1:10:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The thymus gland is supported.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.44,1:10:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, that increases the availability of killer cells, which destroy bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.67,1:10:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,increased immunity, more rapid healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.37,1:10:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a balanced acupuncture system and a positive kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.92,1:10:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is false then makes the body go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.27,1:10:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Blows out the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.67,1:10:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.41,1:10:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is true is recognized by consciousness as pro-life and true, aligned with divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.03,1:10:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,might say.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.38,1:10:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it makes the acupuncture system go strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.63,1:10:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So all you see in the kinesiologic response then is the presence of truth or falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.25,1:10:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the response of the absolute field of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.52,1:10:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.86,1:11:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can tie everything together.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.16,1:11:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution, animal kingdom, the evolution of human consciousness, brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.21,1:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we demonstrated before, we tend to come in together.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.24,1:11:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A group like this, we tend to come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.48,1:11:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We're like, you see, migratory flight or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.76,1:11:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're like a bunch of swans or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.50,1:11:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all swoop onto the planet together.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.20,1:11:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We tend to settle out in various parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.14,1:11:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we all leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.14,1:11:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we swoop back.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.14,1:11:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we swoop back in again.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.12,1:11:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And people tend to congregate like swans, whistling swans, ducks or whatever, in various
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.12,1:11:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.88,1:11:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we ask, if we calibrate the levels of consciousness throughout human life, which
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.70,1:12:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is the formidable task, which I'm just concluding, an encyclopedia of truth, calibrate the level
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.18,1:12:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth of everything in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.28,1:12:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that exists, all the famous people, movies, television, advertising, companies,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.16,1:12:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,corporations, leaders, entertainers.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.40,1:12:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go through the whole world and calibrate the level of consciousness, you better leave
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.37,1:12:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,town.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.37,1:12:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because not everything, essence is not appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.90,1:12:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.72,1:12:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you just say, what's the distribution of the level of consciousness on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.22,1:12:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to understand history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.90,1:12:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.90,1:12:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You start to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.90,1:12:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about 20, 30, 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.90,1:12:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it's a part of history, it's not about time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.90,1:12:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.90,1:12:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you start to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.50,1:12:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mean, that's the way history is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.63,1:12:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some people that have more experience in the world, which are the ones that do it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.63,1:12:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardest, because they don't know how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.63,1:12:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you have more experience in the world, that's why we start to think about history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.18,1:12:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because history starts to be a part of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.18,1:12:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the history has many parts.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.18,1:12:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a part of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.18,1:12:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you look at, once a century, the Pacific Ocean used to be a part of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.18,1:12:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the millennium, US.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.18,1:12:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we have a lot of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.18,1:12:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Central America, 400, the Caribbean Islands in 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.69,1:13:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You see South America generally overall, high 200s to 300.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.69,1:13:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And only one peculiarity in this entire hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.91,1:13:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's Haiti, which calibrates at 55,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.91,1:13:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the home of voodoo and devil worship
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.91,1:13:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and blood sacrifice, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.91,1:13:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So they have their own karmic inheritance
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.91,1:13:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrate at 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.94,1:13:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could say 55 can't cause the world much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.23,1:13:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too crippled by its own pathology.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.94,1:13:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say this hemisphere looks...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.03,1:13:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you came from another universe and you said,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.03,1:13:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what does this universe look like?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.03,1:13:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you come with this map, you'd say,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.03,1:13:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I don't see much trouble here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.03,1:13:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a few arguments, but I don't see any big trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.03,1:13:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next map.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.41,1:13:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now we look at another hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.08,1:13:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this is still North America.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.66,1:13:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we look at another hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.66,1:13:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not too good.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.66,1:13:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.66,1:14:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more general.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.66,1:14:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know what is the condition of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.66,1:14:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, well, here's Australia at 410.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.66,1:14:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see various parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.07,1:14:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see China and India in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.07,1:14:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Mongolia at 175.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.07,1:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that the difficulty is going to be in North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.71,1:14:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that Central Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.71,1:14:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating at 40, is probably going to be destitution.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.71,1:14:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Destitution, poverty, and the helplessness of life at 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.90,1:14:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So this begins to tell you what it is you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.15,1:14:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.15,1:14:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just an explanation of the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.76,1:14:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but specific countries which you can read about in the Daily News.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.76,1:14:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so just leave that for a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.24,1:15:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If things are not happening by causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.65,1:15:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then what is the explanation?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.65,1:15:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The explanation is most of what you witness and read about in the paper
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.16,1:15:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is a field effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.16,1:15:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.16,1:15:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We all know the broken window principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.61,1:15:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody know the broken window principle?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.61,1:15:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody not?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.06,1:15:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the fact that it's a sociologic observation
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.41,1:15:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of why neighborhoods become what they become.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.57,1:15:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you allow one single broken window,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.11,1:15:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to exist in a neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.11,1:15:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it will attract the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.91,1:15:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The first broken window, the next thing that happens is trash.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.91,1:15:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then kids say, oh, let's throw rocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.39,1:15:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then cockroaches, then crime, prostitution, drugs,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.52,1:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and gang dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.80,1:15:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The field begins to attract that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.22,1:16:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that unrepaired, broken factory windows
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.63,1:16:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,result in cockroaches.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.11,1:16:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.98,1:16:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon after the broken windows appear the rats,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.98,1:16:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,appear the drugs, appears the crime,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.98,1:16:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,appears the prostitution, the drug dealing,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.98,1:16:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then the murders, then the arson.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.98,1:16:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you drive through the South Bronx or Brownsville,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.98,1:16:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the blackened windows
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.04,1:16:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because they've all been torched by rival gangs.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.04,1:16:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's going to dominate that block, et cetera?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.55,1:16:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is a field effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.74,1:16:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If things are not within the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.90,1:16:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,causality, then what society does
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.90,1:16:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is use the perpetrator, victim model,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.13,1:16:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to look for who to accuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.05,1:16:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were in England, I got, we read in the newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.59,1:16:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the insulation effect on the,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.59,1:16:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what was that thing that goes out?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.98,1:17:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The spacecraft shuttle, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.52,1:17:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was looking for the bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.78,1:17:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,who to blame for the insulation defect
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.70,1:17:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in the space shuttle crash, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.70,1:17:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the mind thinks dualistically.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.97,1:17:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad. There must be a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.42,1:17:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We should find this bad person.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.42,1:17:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We should blame and vilify this bad person
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.42,1:17:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's responsible for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.70,1:17:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's sort of simplistic third grade, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.70,1:17:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I was thrilled to see the headline.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.11,1:17:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that the problem was due to the overall climate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.21,1:17:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.21,1:17:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the climate of NASA
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.21,1:17:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that accounted for the carelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.21,1:17:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the fault, et cetera, the climate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.42,1:17:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It is like Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.49,1:17:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the climate preceding it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.16,1:18:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Secretary of State Stinson didn't bother to read
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.16,1:18:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the intelligence reports.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.16,1:18:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, gentlemen don't read gentlemen's mail.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.16,1:18:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They turned off reading the Japanese secret code.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.57,1:18:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got, then, Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.57,1:18:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.57,1:18:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could say 9-11 is nothing but
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.57,1:18:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.86,1:18:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watch it on TV,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.86,1:18:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the government was unprepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.50,1:18:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.50,1:18:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,FBI, CIA, military, Pentagon,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.50,1:18:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the city of New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.53,1:18:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of our civilization
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.91,1:18:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,was totally unprepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.46,1:18:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the bad guy? There ain't any.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.46,1:18:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the overall field.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.46,1:18:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The field of negligence and denial
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.62,1:18:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as it was right prior to World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.62,1:18:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing. Denial.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.19,1:18:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, so things are then a field effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.35,1:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not due to cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.35,1:18:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.35,1:19:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were, they'd be incorruptible.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.35,1:19:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Be hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.86,1:19:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we look at the distribution of AIDS,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.44,1:19:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,HIV and AIDS,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.44,1:19:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see that it follows exactly the same pattern
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.44,1:19:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.44,1:19:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the previous map.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.95,1:19:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly the same distribution.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.67,1:19:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, certain things are then
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.15,1:19:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence of the overall field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.15,1:19:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That tells us then where to put our effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.28,1:19:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To lift the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.31,1:19:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lift the level of the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.31,1:19:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all the ships afloat are simultaneously lifted.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.31,1:19:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to lift it is by
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.41,1:19:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,stop looking for the cause
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.61,1:19:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in a Newtonian kind of a manner.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.61,1:19:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at the climate,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.14,1:19:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see the climate has to be changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.14,1:19:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Climate.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.90,1:20:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a book on excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.90,1:20:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellence in business
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.64,1:20:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is what it was specifically about.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.00,1:20:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now with the value of excellence,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.31,1:20:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who remembers the name of the book?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.69,1:20:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very famous book.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.74,1:20:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.41,1:20:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, In Search of Excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.41,1:20:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So what they found was a field.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.41,1:20:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Within that field,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.41,1:20:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,excellence begins to get esteemed for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.41,1:20:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For its own sake, excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.60,1:20:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we need is government
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.02,1:20:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that seeks excellence for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.02,1:20:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For its own sake, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.02,1:20:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As a physician, you're obligated.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.75,1:20:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one I was ever concerned about
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.98,1:20:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is pleasing my own standards.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.98,1:20:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't sleep if you had not served
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.00,1:21:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of excellence within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.45,1:21:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd done the best job you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.45,1:21:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd actually get out of bed
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.90,1:21:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that you left a stone unturned
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.90,1:21:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to help a specific patient with a specific problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.90,1:21:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.90,1:21:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, Alan.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.90,1:21:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get the iodine on him, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.90,1:21:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get the iodine uptake?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.90,1:21:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so how do I think that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.90,1:21:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.90,1:21:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.90,1:21:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the obligation is to yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.90,1:21:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to excellence, to excellence.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.90,1:21:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what anybody out there thinks of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.54,1:21:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Good doctor, bad doctor, immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.54,1:21:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I am concerned with what I think of myself as a physician.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.02,1:21:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, so the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.02,1:21:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,then mean that pride in oneself,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.02,1:21:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,self-esteem,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.02,1:21:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that Bill Cosby spoke about.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.02,1:21:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.02,1:21:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To value yourself, to value life,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.69,1:21:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to value environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.88,1:21:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To pick up the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.88,1:21:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.88,1:21:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you see, when you value life,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.23,1:22:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you create a field in which everybody else values life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.97,1:22:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go into the great beautiful buildings of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.77,1:22:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't see graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.77,1:22:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.41,1:22:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.41,1:22:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You see graffiti in the subways in New York City,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.41,1:22:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,all over everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.73,1:22:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in England, we're going along on the train,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.73,1:22:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,graffiti everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.43,1:22:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to certain places, no graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.43,1:22:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.43,1:22:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the energy of it is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.43,1:22:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You just wouldn't even think of graffiti there.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.43,1:22:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we see the field effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.43,1:22:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.43,1:22:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're going to improve the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.87,1:22:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to need to know what to address.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.87,1:22:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If the world doesn't operate on cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.87,1:22:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're seeing nothing but coalescence of field effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.38,1:22:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then it tells us where we have to put our energy
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.38,1:22:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the field, the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.38,1:22:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I want to improve an area,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.38,1:22:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I move into the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.67,1:22:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just localities in the United States just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.67,1:23:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, you know, if we go around willy-nilly,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.67,1:23:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what does the world look like?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.67,1:23:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we just did some places in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.67,1:23:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in Chicago at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.99,1:23:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States calibrates at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.72,1:23:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicago calibrates at 455, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.78,1:23:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, 455?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.91,1:23:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Chicago?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.91,1:23:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.86,1:23:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, 445, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.86,1:23:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicago calibrates at 445.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.86,1:23:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I was looking at Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.86,1:23:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, man, there's one stunning, beautiful buildings,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.86,1:23:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful architect, beautiful museums.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.86,1:23:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, who was the poet that wrote about Chicago?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.15,1:23:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.75,1:23:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Sandburg, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.75,1:23:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I saw the Chicago of Carl Sandburg.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.75,1:23:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it calibrated at 445.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.75,1:23:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm thinking of lost Americans
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.75,1:23:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who wander to foreign countries,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.75,1:23:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the excuse their family gives is he's trying to find himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.75,1:24:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't find yourself, I suggest you go to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.80,1:24:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At 445.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.80,1:24:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll do better than wandering around civilizations
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.80,1:24:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to calibrate about 145.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.80,1:24:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.80,1:24:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These are just sort of fun things.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.34,1:24:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What are all these things here?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.47,1:24:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,These are just the current dialogue, social dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.42,1:24:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.42,1:24:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't read these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.10,1:24:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, the emergence, the okayness of relativism, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.10,1:24:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when you move away from any kind of an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.10,1:24:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When you move from the absolute, you move to relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.10,1:24:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In relativism, then, you have no right or wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.06,1:24:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing valued, nothing nonvalued, anything goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.06,1:24:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We find the number of hate violence websites.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.66,1:25:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a company called Surf Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.66,1:25:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,From 2000 to 2004, jumped from around 2,700 to 11,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.91,1:25:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,11,000 websites.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.94,1:25:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, well, freedom of speech,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.36,1:25:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the most touted advantage of democracy, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.36,1:25:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.57,1:25:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet Socrates and Aristotle said it'll also be its downfall.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.53,1:25:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because freedom of speech
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.53,1:25:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is a two-edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.53,1:25:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Course in Miracles says
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.53,1:25:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that forgiveness is the only one-edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.98,1:25:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of speech means you give freedom to the lie
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.26,1:25:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,equally with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.26,1:25:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And pretty soon, the mind cannot tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.26,1:25:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Freud pointed out in 1900,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.26,1:25:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the unconscious very often turns things into their opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.26,1:25:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns things into their opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.65,1:26:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't want to refer to it directly,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.65,1:26:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,refers to it as opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.16,1:26:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the downside of freedom of speech
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.16,1:26:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is the abuse of the freedom of speech
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.16,1:26:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the respecting of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.16,1:26:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see 11,000 websites devoted to nothing but hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.16,1:26:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.70,1:26:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to see what happened to freedom of speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.89,1:26:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this one?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.89,1:26:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.89,1:26:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said, what the heck?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.92,1:26:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the Calibrations of Truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.40,1:26:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how is it reflected in our world, in society?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.40,1:26:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We did all the famous books.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.40,1:26:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We did the famous websites.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.40,1:26:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, sites, pyramids.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.40,1:26:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chartres Cathedral went across Europe,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.43,1:26:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,did all the great cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.43,1:26:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.43,1:26:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.43,1:26:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did 200 movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.43,1:26:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that movie reflect?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.43,1:26:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What level of truth does that movie reflect?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.43,1:27:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did 200 movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.96,1:27:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Show us what the effect was, Susie.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.98,1:27:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We did 200 movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.85,1:27:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We did the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.85,1:27:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We did 200 movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.85,1:27:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We did hundreds of places on the planet, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.94,1:27:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's more movies. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.10,1:27:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally she said,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.10,1:27:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I can do any more movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.62,1:27:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Any more slides?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.42,1:27:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.47,1:27:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'll move on from that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.82,1:27:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to show the coalescence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.82,1:27:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this is sort of the field effect
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.82,1:27:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.82,1:27:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we take perpetrator-victim
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.82,1:27:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,projected into the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.82,1:27:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we look for the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.82,1:27:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to correct the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.82,1:27:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We change all kinds of social programs,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.82,1:27:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,only things don't improve.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.82,1:28:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because that's fallacious causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.89,1:28:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let's correlate level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.89,1:28:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with rate of unemployment,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.89,1:28:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,rate of poverty, happiness,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.89,1:28:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and rate of criminality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.02,1:28:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, 600 and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.59,1:28:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.59,1:28:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.59,1:28:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.59,1:28:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.59,1:28:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,500 to 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.91,1:28:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.91,1:28:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.91,1:28:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness rate, 98%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.91,1:28:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of them are loonies.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.23,1:28:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 0.5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.23,1:28:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to figure that one out.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.65,1:28:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, 400 to 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.65,1:28:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment now drops to 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.65,1:28:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 0.5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.65,1:28:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 70%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.65,1:28:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.65,1:28:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibration level, 300 to 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.64,1:28:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment, 7%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.64,1:28:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 1%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.64,1:28:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.64,1:28:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The other 50% need to attend these lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.64,1:28:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.06,1:29:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that must be stealing from the pews or something, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.06,1:29:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.09,1:29:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now what you see is the tremendous change
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.09,1:29:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,at consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.09,1:29:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,At consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.07,1:29:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the unemployment rate goes,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.07,1:29:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's from 8% to 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.42,1:29:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you cross below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.42,1:29:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,unemployment suddenly instead of 8 is 50%, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.42,1:29:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see poverty jumps from 1.5% to 22%.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.42,1:29:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness drops to 15%.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.42,1:29:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And 50% of people below consciousness level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.58,1:29:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,will engage in criminality of one type or another,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.58,1:29:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,even if it's just stealing from the company.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.58,1:29:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time consciousness level gets down to 100 or less,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.50,1:29:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you see unemployment is almost 100%,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.50,1:30:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,poverty is extremely high,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.76,1:30:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,life is okay is down to practically 0%,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.76,1:30:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and criminality becomes almost universal as a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.62,1:30:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So then to affect the quality of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.47,1:30:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to see it's not cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.47,1:30:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a field effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.47,1:30:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence of that which we have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.47,1:30:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That which we have become is that which we value
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.47,1:30:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and hold in high esteem.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.47,1:30:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That which we value and hold in high esteem.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.82,1:30:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the last of the slides?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.82,1:30:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.11,1:30:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.53,1:30:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, this is the last of the one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.53,1:30:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we stop, 3.15, I forget?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.53,1:30:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.53,1:30:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to show the practical application
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.53,1:30:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrating levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.53,1:30:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the history of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.52,1:30:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,peace has prevailed 7% of the history of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.52,1:30:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.52,1:31:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,War has prevailed 93% of the history of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.35,1:31:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.35,1:31:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Fierce statistics to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.57,1:31:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate levels of consciousness now,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.71,1:31:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm proposing is,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.71,1:31:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this sounds like megalomania,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.71,1:31:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is probably, it's okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.71,1:31:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a new science of diplomacy based on
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.34,1:31:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.34,1:31:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't succeed unless you know who you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.44,1:31:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I have a comparison of,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.44,1:31:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,first I had a raw scale without any countries in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.02,1:31:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use the raw scale here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.02,1:31:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called us, or me,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.02,1:31:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is called them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.11,1:31:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here you have the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.11,1:31:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have just the raw numbers.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.11,1:31:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's us, and here's them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.72,1:31:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be your company, your country,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.72,1:31:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your state, your program,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.72,1:31:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,anti-poverty program,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.72,1:32:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,literacy program, whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.72,1:32:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the calibrated level of your program
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.46,1:32:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.71,1:32:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's America overall at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.32,1:32:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's U.S.? 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.32,1:32:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, this is us, 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.48,1:32:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now we calibrate the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.48,1:32:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of what country we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.48,1:32:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to know three things.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.48,1:32:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to know the calibrated level of the leader,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.48,1:32:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the people, and the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.70,1:32:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to know all three.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.83,1:32:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often there's a big disparity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.83,1:32:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,One country I'm holding in mind right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.83,1:32:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the leader is extremely high,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.83,1:32:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the government is completely rotten and dissolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.96,1:32:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and the people are loving, wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.73,1:32:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to pay off for everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.73,1:32:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The government's rotten.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.73,1:32:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy at the head calibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.73,1:32:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really high.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.73,1:32:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the people are adorable,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.73,1:32:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but just the government is rotten through and through.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.73,1:32:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got to know the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.73,1:33:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,between who you're dealing with,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.73,1:33:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,diplomatically, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.91,1:33:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's us.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.91,1:33:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here's the calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.91,1:33:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of who you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.04,1:33:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say, let's take a country
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.04,1:33:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Middle East, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.04,1:33:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.36,1:33:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dealing with somebody at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.36,1:33:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're dealing with Afghanistan
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.36,1:33:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and various militant countries.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.09,1:33:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't talk any kind of sense
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.09,1:33:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're talking your language
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.09,1:33:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're speaking a different language.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.12,1:33:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the office, there's a psychoanalyst,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.12,1:33:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a psychiatrist, there's a physician.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.12,1:33:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't expect the patient to be where I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.12,1:33:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I go where they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.12,1:33:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my job to understand them,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.12,1:33:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not for them to understand me.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.12,1:33:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to understand who I'm dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.66,1:33:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I go into Afghanistan and I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.66,1:33:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,young man, please give me your gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.73,1:34:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like you to have the freedom of the vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.32,1:34:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Democracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.70,1:34:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of speech, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.70,1:34:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Except the gun's the only thing he's got.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.09,1:34:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives in a culture in which,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.86,1:34:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,without a gun, he's nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.86,1:34:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,With a gun, he's employable.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.86,1:34:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He can live, make a living.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.86,1:34:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He gains respect, has self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.86,1:34:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a gun, he's nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.86,1:34:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.92,1:34:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't read or write. Pathetic. Stone age.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.92,1:34:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.44,1:34:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, if we know where the other people are,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.63,1:34:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can talk to them at their level.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.40,1:34:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would democracy appeal to people like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.40,1:34:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joke, democracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.40,1:34:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an inflated ego about democracy,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.04,1:34:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how wonderful it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.04,1:34:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How wonderful it is for who?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.04,1:34:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For these people here?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.39,1:34:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What would democracy do for these people?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.39,1:34:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't spell it to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.22,1:35:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.56,1:35:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How would democracy improve your life?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.56,1:35:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There, now that would start to make sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.56,1:35:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the gain?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.56,1:35:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Below consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.98,1:35:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,people are only interested in gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.98,1:35:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.98,1:35:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.81,1:35:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Foreign aid, where does it go?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.81,1:35:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes to enrich the people at the top
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.81,1:35:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,who have siphoned it all off,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.81,1:35:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the poorest are just as poor as ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.81,1:35:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's real?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.38,1:35:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Utilizing calibrating levels of truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.38,1:35:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we could make our efforts in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.38,1:35:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,far more beneficial
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.38,1:35:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by understanding a different paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.42,1:35:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy things come about as a consequence of the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.42,1:35:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not as a consequence of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.42,1:35:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pour millions and millions
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.42,1:35:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of dollars into this anti-poverty program
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.42,1:35:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you haven't changed the incidence of poverty at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.42,1:35:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't even addressed where it's coming from.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.42,1:35:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Where it's coming from.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.42,1:35:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So this would be a science of international diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.86,1:36:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.86,1:36:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched embarrassing interviews
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.86,1:36:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in which an American commentator
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.24,1:36:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is talking to the head of the biggest nation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.37,1:36:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and insulting him.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.53,1:36:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your civil rights violations in your country?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.38,1:36:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Happily, he was a very cool guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.72,1:36:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate's quite high, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.82,1:36:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, well, you do have a few problems
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.82,1:36:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in your own country.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.82,1:36:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Crime, divorce, drugs, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.82,1:36:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, America does have a few guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.55,1:36:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,50% divorce rate, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.70,1:36:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Drugs, crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.70,1:36:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Highest rate of imprisonment of any country.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.70,1:36:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You do have a few problems of your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.70,1:36:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So he took it very gently.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.74,1:36:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought it was very disrespectful.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.74,1:36:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The person he was talking to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.18,1:36:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated around 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.18,1:37:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Brilliant man.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.87,1:37:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the head of the biggest nation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.87,1:37:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.87,1:37:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's this interviewer,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.00,1:37:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,cocky, adolescent, typically American,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.00,1:37:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,challenging him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.00,1:37:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, how disrespectful.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.00,1:37:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how America gets its reputation.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.26,1:37:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Disrespect for the reality
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.26,1:37:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in which other people are living.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.02,1:37:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So calibrating the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.02,1:37:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,should give us humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.40,1:37:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Get real.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.40,1:37:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Get to see what people,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.56,1:37:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what their level of consciousness is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.56,1:37:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Who they really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.56,1:37:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is their leader?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.56,1:37:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is their government?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.56,1:37:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And which is the people?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.56,1:37:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the people, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.56,1:37:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the government?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.23,1:37:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To bring about a greater likelihood of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.90,1:37:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the history of the world, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.90,1:37:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood has been,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.80,1:37:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence of falsehood has been war.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.80,1:37:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And peace only comes about as a consequence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.43,1:38:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood is always the consequence of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.43,1:38:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It is never the consequence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.56,1:38:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So an indirect truth instead of falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.91,1:38:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is to increase the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.42,1:38:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that peace will prevail.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.42,1:38:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,By our combined intention, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.95,1:38:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if we value peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.98,1:38:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to value truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.21,1:38:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth above positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.50,1:38:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway to God through truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.85,1:38:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotional non-duality means
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.17,1:38:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway to God through devotion
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.17,1:38:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.39,1:38:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is revealed by truth itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.39,1:38:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotional non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.42,1:38:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the last?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.67,1:38:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.89,1:38:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then the summation of
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.59,1:38:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,going through the world and all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.59,1:38:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,since the beginning of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.59,1:38:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating the levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.66,1:39:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.66,1:39:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on up through the animal kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.66,1:39:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the progression of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.66,1:39:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending the ego into spiritual reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.66,1:39:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and, hmm,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.10,1:39:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the ongoingness of calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.10,1:39:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.10,1:39:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way up to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.20,1:39:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bhagavad Gita at 900.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.20,1:39:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The great gurus of Aryan culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.42,1:39:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The sages of old already knew
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.42,1:39:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,truth at levels of 900 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.86,1:39:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,900 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.86,1:39:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Before present-day religions were born.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.86,1:39:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Long before the birth of Jesus or Buddha
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.12,1:39:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or Muhammad,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.25,1:39:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the great sages calibrated at 900 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.25,1:39:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.25,1:39:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.44,1:39:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, O Lord, we do pray to Thee
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.44,1:39:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that Thy truth prevail
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.44,1:39:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.89,1:40:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.89,1:40:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.89,1:40:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
